utrients and oxygen needed for growth. Research findings show that Deer placenta has similar properties to that of the human placenta. It resembles the human placenta very closely chemically and biologically. It has been accepted as the premier source of the placenta because of its rich source of Stem cells. Stem Cell therapy is one of the few treatments that are used to stimulate the body\'s rejuvenation system and cell renewal.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Squalene</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Squalene is a poly-unsaturated hydrocarbon liquid that occurs naturally, ubiquitously in human tissue in small amounts. The most abundant source of Squalene is from the livers of Sharks. Squalene stimulates the metabolism of the body by supplying oxygen to the tissues.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">There are many health benefits to consuming Squalene.</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Cell-Invigorating</strong>: Squalene revitalizes weakened body cells and helps revive cell generation.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Purifying</strong>: Squalene helps clean, purify, and detoxify the blood from toxins, facilitating blood circulation. It cleanses the gastrointestinal tract and kidneys, causing better bowel movement and urination.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Curbing of Bad Cholesterol</strong>: Squalene has good cholesterol that is made up of high-density lipid (HDL).</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Anti-Aging</strong>: Since Squalene prevents cell damage, healthy cells are produced daily.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Oxygen Control</strong>: Squalene carries oxygen at the cellular level, causing further improvement in organ function through cellular metabolism.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Sterilizing</strong>: combating the growth of various germs such as coliform bacilli.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Other Actions</strong>: Squalene - reduces various aches and pains - helps body organs such as the kidneys, liver and gallbladder function properly - helps digestive system function properly by reducing gastro ptosis conditions, helping to shrink hemorrhoids and acts as a relaxant, giving added vigor and vitality without the hyperactivity associated with other food supplements.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Evening Primrose oil (Gamma Linolenic Acid)</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Evening primrose oil is extracted from the seeds of the evening primrose plant (Oenothera biennis) - a wildflower that grows in eastern and central North America. Evening primrose is mainly used for the production of its oil, which has a range of therapeutic properties. The oil is commonly used to help reduce the pains associated with premenstrual stress syndrome (PMS) and for its therapeutic benefits for the skin of the face. There are other possible therapeutic properties of the oil as well. Evening primrose seeds have very high levels of the essential fatty acid \"gamma-Linolenic acid\" (GLA), also known as \"omega-6\". Omega-6 is crucial for maintaining a joint\'s cell structure and function. The U.S. National Institutes of Health says omega-6 could also help slow blood clotting, treat symptoms of skin conditions and help alleviate itchiness caused by dermatitis and eczema.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Grape seed extract (equiv. to 12000mg)</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">The grape seed extract is a derivative of grape seeds that are extremely rich in antioxidants and oligomeric proanthocyanidin complexes (OPCs). The extract has been linked to a wide range of possible therapeutic properties because it is highly regarded as alternative medicine. Studies revealed some evidence suggesting extensive health benefits like wound healing and treating conditions such as high cholesterol, atherosclerosis, macular degeneration, poor circulation, heart disease, nerve damage, as well as preventing cancer. It further improves bone strength, Reduces edema (swelling), prevents cognitive decline.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Japanese Knotweed Root extract</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">For centuries, Chinese and Japanese cultures have used Japanese Knotweed (as well as a similar variety known as Giant Knotweed) in traditional health preparations. Japanese Knotweed has long been used traditionally to maintain healthy blood circulation and healthy inflammatory processes. Japanese Knotweed is revered for its many health benefits because it’s a great source of resveratrol that supports heart health and antioxidant levels. Japanese Knotweed is tenacious, difficult to kill and can withstand extreme temperatures. Scientists believe that tenacious, survival qualities give the plant numerous health benefits. It’s the strong concentration of Resveratrol at the root of the Japanese Knotweed which makes it an adaptable “survival plant.” Japanese Knotweed is known to have the most concentrated form of Resveratrol, which supports cardiovascular health, antioxidant levels, youthful appearance, and energy.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Resveratrol</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Resveratrol is a member of a group of plant compounds called polyphenols. These compounds are thought to have antioxidant properties, protecting the body against the kind of damage linked to conditions such as cancer and heart disease. Resveratrol is found in the skin of red grapes, but other sources include peanuts and berries and herbs. Most resveratrol capsules sold in the U.S. contain extracts from the Japanese and Chinese knotweed plant Polygonum cuspidatum. Resveratrol has gained a lot of attention for its reported anti-aging and disease-combating benefits. Researchers believe that resveratrol activates the SIRT1 gene, a biological mechanism that seems to protect the body against the harmful effects of obesity and the diseases of aging.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Can Dermacel™ be taken with other medications?</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Dermacel is not a drug or medicine but a nutritional supplement. It would not interfere with your medication and supplements. Take 2 capsules daily at any time of the day. It is safe for consumption and has been recommended for anyone above the age of 18 years old</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">STEM CELL FAQS</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">What are Stem Cells?</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Stem cells are mother cells that have the potential to become any type of cell in the body. One of the main characteristics of stem cells is their ability to self-renew or multiply while maintaining the potential to develop into other types of cells.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Our human body depends on adult stem cells in the bone marrow to repair damage and stay healthy. The vital role adult stem cells play in both health and disease is one of the greatest health discoveries of modern times.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">What are the characteristics of stem cells?</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">One of the main characteristics of stem cells is their ability to self-renew or multiply while maintaining the potential to develop into other types of cells.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Our human body depends on adult stem cells in the bone marrow to repair damage and stay healthy. The vital role adult stem cells play in both health and disease is one of the greatest health discoveries of modern times.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Does the human body require stem cells?</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Our human body depends on adult stem cells in the bone marrow to repair damage and stay healthy. The vital role adult stem cells play in both health and disease is one of the greatest health discoveries of modern times.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">How does that damage our body?</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">The decline of adult stem cells can lead to un-repaired damage in virtually any body part, leading to tissue breakdown, aging and loss of health. Without active, vigorous adult stem cells, good health is compromised long-term. Scientific anti-aging research shows adult stem cell release rates from the bone marrow drop at an astonishing rate as we age.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">How does stem cell affect our aging?</strong></p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">As we age our stem cell production from our bone marrow declines. This is one of the causes of aging as well as exposure to various environmental (and sometimes dietary) toxins, stress, oxidation, inflammation, and hormone decline.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">The decline of adult stem cells can lead to un-repaired damage in virtually any body part, leading to tissue breakdown, aging and loss of health. Without active, vigorous adult stem cells, good health is compromised long-term. Scientific anti-aging research shows adult stem cell release rates from the bone marrow drop at an astonishing rate as we age.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">35 years - the stem cell release rate drops by 45%</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px